1
00:00:02,436 --> 00:00:04,169
ALL RIGHT, COULD IT BE BEHIND
DOOR NUMBER ONE, TWO OR THREE?

2
00:00:04,237 --> 00:00:08,339
AND YOU HAVE FIRST CHOICE
RIGHT NOW, KATHY.
WHAT DOOR DO YOU WANT?

3
00:00:08,408 --> 00:00:11,042
<i>[ Kathy ]</i>
<i>THREE.</i>
<i>DOOR NUMBER THREE.</i>

4
00:00:11,111 --> 00:00:15,547
<i>AND, DEBBIE? DEBBIE,</i>
<i>JUST FOR THE FUN OF IT--</i>

5
00:00:15,616 --> 00:00:18,383
<i>JUST FOR THE FUN OF IT,</i>
<i>WHICH ONE WOULD YOU HAVE CHOSEN</i>
<i>IF YOU WENT FOR IT?</i>

6
00:00:18,452 --> 00:00:21,520
<i>[ Debbie ] TWO.</i>
<i>NUMBER TWO.</i>
<i>WHAT WAS BEHIND NUMBER TWO?</i>

7
00:00:21,589 --> 00:00:24,556
<i>JUST TWO--</i>
<i>$2,000 IN CASH,</i>

8
00:00:24,625 --> 00:00:29,160
<i>BECAUSE THE SUPER DEAL</i>
<i>WAS BEHIND... NUMBER ONE!</i>

9
00:00:29,229 --> 00:00:31,930
<i>AND NUMBER THREE</i>
<i>HAD THE $1,000.</i>

10
00:00:31,999 --> 00:00:34,699
<i>[ Knocking ]</i>
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>READY TO TAKE THE PLUNGE?</i>

11
00:00:34,768 --> 00:00:38,103
READY.
IT'S MY "BIG DEAL OF THE DAY."

12
00:00:40,241 --> 00:00:42,741
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>JAROD MUST'VE SCREWED UP BAD...</i>

13
00:00:42,809 --> 00:00:45,877
IF THEY SENT
THREE OF YA OUT HERE
TO CLOSE HIM DOWN.

14
00:00:45,946 --> 00:00:49,614
YOU SURE THAT YOU'RE HIS
AMWAY FIELD REPRESENTATIVES?

15
00:00:49,683 --> 00:00:54,186
DO YOU REALLY THINK
THAT WE COULD FOOL SOMEONE
AS SMART AS YOURSELF?

16
00:00:54,254 --> 00:00:57,889
WELL, UH, I-I GUESS
IT'S THAT AMWAY THING.

17
00:00:57,958 --> 00:01:03,462
UH, I JUST NEVER THOUGHT
OF JAROD AS A GLYCERIN
AND HONEY SOAP KIND OF GUY.

18
00:01:03,530 --> 00:01:06,264
THAT IS WHAT YOU PEOPLE SELL,
ISN'T IT? SOAP?

19
00:01:06,333 --> 00:01:09,100
YEAH, UH, EVERYTHING
FROM, UH, BABY SHAMPOO...

20
00:01:09,169 --> 00:01:10,735
<i>TO, UH, INDUSTRIAL-STRENGTH</i>
<i>POOL CLEANER.</i>

21
00:01:10,804 --> 00:01:12,804
THAT'D BE GOOD FOR YOU.

22
00:01:12,872 --> 00:01:15,307
<i> OH, LOOK.</i>

23
00:01:15,375 --> 00:01:17,742
THE MATCH GAME,
THE HOME VERSION.

24
00:01:17,811 --> 00:01:21,480
UH, JAROD, HE'S A--
HE'S A REGULAR
LIGHTNING ROUND LUNATIC.

25
00:01:21,549 --> 00:01:24,482
<i>WHEN HE'S NOT SURFIN' THE WAVES,</i>
<i>HE'S SURFIN'</i>
<i>THE GAME SHOW CHANNEL.</i>

26
00:01:24,551 --> 00:01:26,652
PARKER?

27
00:01:27,721 --> 00:01:29,420
<i> PUSHING THE LIMITS.</i>

28
00:01:29,489 --> 00:01:33,124
<i>TAKING RISKS.</i>
<i>CONFESSIONS OF</i>
<i>AN ADRENALINE JUNKIE.</i>

29
00:01:33,194 --> 00:01:37,095
WHAT ARE WE TALKIN' ABOUT HERE,
SYD? JAROD KNIEVEL
JUMPING BUICKS AT CAESARS?

30
00:01:37,164 --> 00:01:40,999
IT'S DAREDEVIL STUFF,
YOU KNOW? HE'S ALWAYS
DOING DANGEROUS THINGS,

31
00:01:41,067 --> 00:01:45,169
<i> LIKE NIGHT SURFING</i>
<i> AND STREET LUGE AND--</i>

32
00:01:45,238 --> 00:01:49,007
HE EVEN STRAPPED THAT
BULLETPROOF VEST ON ONCE AND
HE HAD ME SHOOT HIM BLINDFOLDED!

33
00:01:49,076 --> 00:01:52,911
<i>ALL MANIFESTATIONS OF</i>
<i>AN OBSESSION WITH RISK-TAKING.</i>

34
00:01:52,980 --> 00:01:57,148
WHAT KIND OF TRAINING
DO YOU PUT YOUR SALESPEOPLE
THROUGH, ACTUALLY?

35
00:01:57,217 --> 00:01:59,918
WE'LL SEND YOU A BROCHURE.
DR. QUACKENBUSH,

36
00:01:59,987 --> 00:02:03,689
ONCE AGAIN,
YOUR DIAGNOSIS HAS COME
TOO LATE TO FIND JAROD.

37
00:02:03,757 --> 00:02:07,493
<i>WELL, NOT THAT LATE.</i>
<i>HE LEFT LESS THAN AN HOUR AGO.</i>

38
00:02:07,561 --> 00:02:09,695
<i> WAS THAT WITH OR WITHOUT</i>
<i> HIS BLINDFOLD?</i>

39
00:02:09,763 --> 00:02:11,863
YOU DON'T NEED A BLINDFOLD
TO JUMP OFF A BRIDGE.

40
00:02:15,502 --> 00:02:18,436
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>YOU SURE YOU WANT TO STAY</i>
<i>WITH THIS OLD CORD, JAROD?</i>

41
00:02:18,505 --> 00:02:20,671
YOU'VE DONE 295
ON THIS ONE.

42
00:02:20,740 --> 00:02:24,576
WELL, I ONLY REALLY NEED IT
TO LAST 296.

43
00:02:32,586 --> 00:02:35,019
[ Yelling ]

44
00:02:37,724 --> 00:02:40,859
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>
<i>THERE ARE PRETENDERS AMONG US.</i>

45
00:02:40,928 --> 00:02:42,860
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>I WAS TAKEN FROM MY FAMILY.</i>

46
00:02:42,929 --> 00:02:46,798
<i>THIRTY-SIX HOURS AND HE'S</i>
<i>ALREADY DEMONSTRATING MORE</i>
<i>TALENT THAN ANY OF OUR OTHERS.</i>

47
00:02:46,867 --> 00:02:49,968
<i>HOW MANY PEOPLE DIED</i>
<i>BECAUSE OF WHAT I THOUGHT UP?</i>

48
00:02:50,037 --> 00:02:53,472
SINCE I BROKE OUT,
I'VE SPENT EVERY MOMENT
SEARCHING FOR MY PAST.

49
00:02:53,541 --> 00:02:54,740
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>HE'S A PRETENDER--</i>

50
00:02:54,808 --> 00:02:58,577
<i>A GENIUS WHO CAN BECOME</i>
<i>ANYONE THAT HE WANTS TO BE.</i>

51
00:02:58,646 --> 00:03:00,645
- THE CENTRE WANTS HIM ALIVE.
- PREFERABLY.

52
00:03:00,714 --> 00:03:03,615
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>HE DEFENDS THE WEAK AND ABUSED.</i>

53
00:03:03,683 --> 00:03:05,450
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>LIFE'S A GIFT.</i>

54
00:03:16,162 --> 00:03:18,162
-<i> YOU A DOCTOR?</i>
- I AM TODAY.

55
00:03:24,838 --> 00:03:27,406
<i> MR. GOLTZ'S M.R.I. REVEALS</i>
<i> A CLOSED FRACTURE...</i>

56
00:03:27,474 --> 00:03:29,674
OF THE RIGHT PARIETAL BONE
WITH A SUBDURAL HEMATOMA.

57
00:03:29,743 --> 00:03:31,676
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>WE'VE INSERTED A C.S.F. SHUNT,</i>

58
00:03:31,745 --> 00:03:34,579
<i>SO WE SHOULD KNOW MORE</i>
<i>ONCE HIS EDEMA'S RESOLVED.</i>

59
00:03:34,648 --> 00:03:37,582
I NOTICE ON HIS ADMISSION CHART
THE PRESENCE OF
GLASS FRAGMENTS IN HIS HAIR.

60
00:03:37,651 --> 00:03:39,717
<i>[ Man ] IT'S A MYSTERY.</i>
<i>I ASSUMED THEY CAME</i>
<i>FROM HIS GLASSES.</i>

61
00:03:39,786 --> 00:03:41,719
<i>BUT HIS MOTHER SAYS</i>
<i>TONY DOESN'T WEAR THEM.</i>

62
00:03:41,788 --> 00:03:44,823
COULD IT HAVE BEEN
A SPORTS GOGGLE OF SOME KIND?
NO. INDUSTRIAL-GRADE GLASS.

63
00:03:44,892 --> 00:03:47,092
I, UH, DID
A LAB ANALYSIS MYSELF.

64
00:03:47,161 --> 00:03:49,427
YOU DID IT,
NOT THE POLICE?

65
00:03:49,496 --> 00:03:53,698
<i>[ Man ] THEY'RE TREATING</i>
<i>THE ENTIRE GOLTZ CASE</i>
<i>AS A BUNGEE STUNT GONE BAD.</i>

66
00:03:53,767 --> 00:03:55,934
OPEN AND SHUT.
NO MORE, NO LESS.

67
00:04:00,140 --> 00:04:03,041
<i> TONY? HONEY,</i>
<i> COME ON BACK HOME.</i>

68
00:04:03,109 --> 00:04:05,410
<i> YOUR SISTER AND I</i>
<i> MISS YOU SO.</i>

69
00:04:05,479 --> 00:04:07,212
<i> I ALWAYS KEEP</i>
<i> MY FAMILY CLOSE TOO.</i>

70
00:04:07,281 --> 00:04:09,581
SORRY. YOU MUST BE
DR. NICHOLS.

71
00:04:09,650 --> 00:04:13,317
- CALL ME JAROD.
- OH, PLEASE, SIT DOWN.

72
00:04:13,386 --> 00:04:16,488
<i>WHEN TONY WAKES UP,</i>
<i>I JUST WANT HIM TO REMEMBER.</i>

73
00:04:16,556 --> 00:04:20,125
ACTUALLY,
I DIDN'T THINK I'D EVER
SEE THESE PHOTOS AGAIN.

74
00:04:20,194 --> 00:04:23,094
I THOUGHT TONY'S WALLET
HAD BEEN LOST IN THE ACCIDENT,

75
00:04:23,163 --> 00:04:25,796
BUT SOMEBODY FOUND IT
AT THE NURSES' STATION
THIS MORNING.

76
00:04:25,865 --> 00:04:28,066
<i>IT WAS LEFT IN THAT ENVELOPE</i>
<i>WRAPPED IN WAX PAPER.</i>

77
00:04:29,403 --> 00:04:33,671
WELL, AT LEAST THE PICTURES
WERE STILL THERE.

78
00:04:38,144 --> 00:04:40,344
<i>HIS SISTER CARRIE TOOK THOSE</i>
<i>AT HIS LAST BIRTHDAY.</i>

79
00:04:40,413 --> 00:04:42,614
A WEEK LATER, HE WAS OFF
LOOKING FOR HIS DAD.

80
00:04:43,684 --> 00:04:45,816
HE WAS SEARCHING FOR HIS FATHER?

81
00:04:45,885 --> 00:04:48,253
HIS FATHER RODE OFF
ON A DIRT BIKE IN '91
AND NEVER LOOKED BACK.

82
00:04:48,321 --> 00:04:51,656
SEARCHING FOR YOUR FAMILY.
IT'S INSTINCT.

83
00:04:51,725 --> 00:04:54,659
NOW HIS--
HIS SISTER CARRIE'S
DOING IT.

84
00:04:54,728 --> 00:04:58,129
NOT LONG AFTER WE CAME
OUT HERE TO LOOK AFTER TONY,
SHE JUST TOOK OFF.

85
00:04:58,198 --> 00:05:03,035
I'M JUST HOPING THAT SOMEDAY,
WE'LL ALL BE SMILING
LIKE IN THOSE PICTURES AGAIN.

86
00:05:03,103 --> 00:05:07,538
THE BEST THERAPY FOR HIM
IS TO HEAR THE VOICE
OF HIS FAMILY AND HIS FRIENDS.

87
00:05:07,608 --> 00:05:12,343
I GUESS THAT'S JUST ME NOW.
HIS FRIENDS USED TO COME BY
AND VISIT, BUT THEY STOPPED.

88
00:05:12,412 --> 00:05:14,545
- WHERE ARE THEY?
- I DON'T KNOW.

89
00:05:14,614 --> 00:05:16,881
<i> HE AND HIS DAREDEVIL</i>
<i> FRIEND ZED...</i>

90
00:05:16,950 --> 00:05:19,917
USED TO RIDE MOTORCYCLES
OUT AT A PLACE
CALLED WILLOW RIDGE.

91
00:05:19,986 --> 00:05:22,887
<i> I GUESS ZED'S</i>
<i> RIDING ALONE NOW.</i>

92
00:05:41,942 --> 00:05:44,042
<i>♪♪ [ Rock, Indistinct ]</i>

93
00:06:09,569 --> 00:06:13,071
[ Honking ]
[ Tires Screeching ]

94
00:06:21,315 --> 00:06:24,015
YOU OKAY?

95
00:06:24,084 --> 00:06:28,086
HEY, NO PROBLEM.
I ALWAYS WANTED TO BE
A HOOD ORNAMENT.

96
00:06:28,155 --> 00:06:30,421
I'LL TAKE THAT AS A "YES."

97
00:06:30,490 --> 00:06:33,624
YOU KNOW, THE WAY
YOU FLEW UP MY TAILPIPE,
I THOUGHT YOU WERE A COP.

98
00:06:33,693 --> 00:06:37,228
NOT TODAY.
ARE YOU SURE YOU'RE ALL RIGHT?

99
00:06:37,297 --> 00:06:39,698
NO, IT'S OKAY.
THE CHICK CAN HANDLE IT.

100
00:06:39,767 --> 00:06:43,034
CHICKS?
THEY CALL ME JAROD.

101
00:06:43,103 --> 00:06:45,737
- FRIENDS CALL ME SHAY.
- HMM.

102
00:06:45,805 --> 00:06:48,473
FRIENDS LIKE ZED?

103
00:06:48,541 --> 00:06:52,210
- YOU KNOW ZED?
- I UNDERSTAND THAT HE AND
HIS FRIENDS RACE THIS ROAD.

104
00:06:52,279 --> 00:06:55,980
HUH. WELL, MAYBE
I WAS RIGHT ABOUT YOU.
MAYBE YOU ARE A COP.

105
00:06:56,049 --> 00:06:59,217
JUST SOMEBODY TRYIN'
TO FIGHT THE BOREDOM.

106
00:06:59,285 --> 00:07:03,287
OH, BY THE WAY,
NICE RACING.

107
00:07:08,928 --> 00:07:11,229
[ Engine Sputtering ]

108
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:17,502
IT'S NOT EXACTLY
A POLICE ESCORT,
BUT I HAVE AN EXTRA SEAT.

109
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:29,181
<i>ASK ME, SPEED RACER'S</i>
<i>KISSED THE ASPHALT...</i>

110
00:07:29,249 --> 00:07:31,583
ONE TOO MANY TIMES
WITHOUT A HELMET.

111
00:07:31,651 --> 00:07:33,918
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>
<i>COULD BE A PSYCHOTIC CRY</i>
<i>FOR HELP.</i>

112
00:07:33,987 --> 00:07:37,255
HI, SIS.
SO I HEARD JAROD NEVER
CAME BACK TO HIS LAIR.

113
00:07:37,324 --> 00:07:39,257
ANY LUCK DECIPHERING
HIS NEW OCCUPATION?

114
00:07:39,326 --> 00:07:43,995
DON'T QUOTE ME,
BUT I THINK HE MORPHED INTO
THE HUMAN CANNONBALL.

115
00:07:44,064 --> 00:07:49,267
<i>JAROD SEEMS TO BE EXHIBITING</i>
<i>ALL THE SIGNS OF AN OBSESSION</i>
<i>WITH EXTREME THRILL-SEEKING.</i>

116
00:07:49,336 --> 00:07:51,269
HMM.
MAYBE HE'S REJUVENATING.

117
00:07:51,337 --> 00:07:53,972
SOME JUMP OFF CLIFFS,
OTHERS SEEK RELIGION.

118
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:56,875
I, FOR ONE, REPLENISH MY SOUL
BY GOING BACK TO NATURE.

119
00:07:56,943 --> 00:08:00,445
OH.
WHAT, SURPRISED TO FIND
I LIKE TO CAMP?

120
00:08:00,513 --> 00:08:03,014
NO. SURPRISED TO FIND
YOU HAVE A SOUL.

121
00:08:03,082 --> 00:08:07,052
ON THAT LOVING NOTE, I'M OFF
TO THE WILDS FOR THREE DAYS.

122
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:09,654
MY OFFICE WILL KNOW
HOW TO REACH ME.

123
00:08:11,524 --> 00:08:14,492
I CAN DIE NOW.
I'VE SEEN IT ALL.

124
00:08:14,561 --> 00:08:17,562
[ Chuckles ]
YOU WANNA BET?

125
00:08:17,630 --> 00:08:20,064
THEY WERE JUST DELIVERED.

126
00:08:21,601 --> 00:08:23,534
SCRATCH "HUMAN CANNONBALL."

127
00:08:23,603 --> 00:08:28,006
- HE'S FREAKIN' CHUCK BARRIS.
- WELL, ACTUALLY, MONTY HALL.

128
00:08:28,074 --> 00:08:31,343
AND WHAT EXACTLY IS THE DEAL
WITH JAROD'S BIG DEAL, BROOTS?

129
00:08:31,411 --> 00:08:33,978
WE OPEN DOOR NUMBER ONE
WITH THIS KEY.

130
00:08:34,047 --> 00:08:36,213
- WHAT ABOUT THE OTHER TWO?
- TIME-LOCKED.

131
00:08:36,283 --> 00:08:38,916
THEY'LL OPEN AT
PREDETERMINED INTERVALS.
<i>[ Miss Parker ] GIVE ME THAT.</i>

132
00:08:38,985 --> 00:08:42,753
OKAY, QUIZMASTER,
WHAT IS BEHIND DOOR NUMBER ONE?

133
00:08:44,057 --> 00:08:46,090
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>LOOKS LIKE A GIANT</i>
<i>FORTUNE COOKIE.</i>

134
00:08:46,159 --> 00:08:48,359
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>IT IS A GIANT FORTUNE COOKIE.</i>

135
00:08:52,499 --> 00:08:54,999
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>SO WHAT'S OUR FUTURE HOLD?</i>

136
00:08:55,068 --> 00:08:57,535
IT'S NOT ABOUT OUR FUTURE.
IT'S ABOUT THE PAST.

137
00:08:57,604 --> 00:08:59,537
IT'S A DINNER BILL
FROM A FEW WEEKS AGO.

138
00:08:59,606 --> 00:09:03,574
"THE HIDDEN TRUTH."
AND THE WAITRESS
WAS CALLED MAY LIN.

139
00:09:03,643 --> 00:09:07,345
<i>"THE HIDDEN TRUTH." YEAH.</i>
<i>THAT'S THE CHINESE RESTAURANT</i>
<i>I PASS BY ON MY WAY HERE.</i>

140
00:09:07,414 --> 00:09:09,447
- I'VE NEVER BEEN THERE.
- ME EITHER. YOU, SYD?

141
00:09:09,515 --> 00:09:12,784
I DON'T EAT RICE.

142
00:09:12,853 --> 00:09:15,553
<i> SO WHAT DO YOU THINK</i>
<i> IT MEANS, MISS PARKER?</i>

143
00:09:15,622 --> 00:09:18,857
THAT WE NEED RESERVATIONS.

144
00:09:22,395 --> 00:09:24,428
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>YOU LOSE.</i>

145
00:09:31,804 --> 00:09:34,038
<i>[ Shay ]</i>
<i>YO, ZEDDIE, JOJO, MACKEY.</i>

146
00:09:34,107 --> 00:09:36,607
WHAT UP, SHAY?
WHERE YOU BEEN, CHILLIN'
ON A BEACH WITH A COLDIE?

147
00:09:36,676 --> 00:09:38,142
JUST RIDING.
<i>YEAH?</i>

148
00:09:38,211 --> 00:09:40,578
<i> YOU GONNA DO THAT LUGE</i>
<i> IN A WET SUIT?</i>

149
00:09:40,647 --> 00:09:43,047
I'VE BEEN SURFIN' TODAY,
DARLIN'. JOJO?

150
00:09:43,116 --> 00:09:45,650
BUT I HEAR THAT WHALING STRETCH
OF ROAD IN THE GLEN'S
GETTIN' SHUT DOWN NEXT WEEK.

151
00:09:45,718 --> 00:09:49,387
-<i> SO THEY'RE DROPPING THE HILL?</i>
- NOT SOON ENOUGH. NAME'S ZED.

152
00:09:49,456 --> 00:09:53,158
-JAROD.
-HE'S NOT SOME JEHOVAH'S WITNESS
KNOCKIN' ON MY DOOR, IS HE?

153
00:09:53,226 --> 00:09:55,760
<i> WELL, I'VE WITNESSED A LOT,</i>
<i> BUT NEVER JEHOVAH.</i>

154
00:09:55,828 --> 00:09:59,263
THAT'S GOOD, 'CAUSE I'M BROKE.
AND I HAVEN'T SEEN GOD.

155
00:09:59,333 --> 00:10:01,899
AT LEAST NOT SINCE I HAD
THAT AWESOME MELTDOWN LUGIN'
A CANYON LAST WEEK, HEY, GUYS?

156
00:10:01,968 --> 00:10:03,234
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>RIGHT ON!</i>

157
00:10:03,303 --> 00:10:06,170
- YOU LIKE TO RIDE, "J"?
- ANYTHING AND EVERYTHING.

158
00:10:06,239 --> 00:10:08,305
WHAT DO YOU DO FOR A LIVING?

159
00:10:08,375 --> 00:10:11,442
WELL, I SEEM TO HAVE TROUBLE
HOLDING DOWN A STEADY JOB.

160
00:10:11,511 --> 00:10:13,444
I GET BORED PRETTY EASILY.

161
00:10:13,513 --> 00:10:15,780
AH, BOREDOM.
THE ENDLESS BOWEL.

162
00:10:15,849 --> 00:10:19,050
- WHAT ABOUT YOURSELF?
- A JOB HERE, A JOB THERE,
YOU KNOW.

163
00:10:19,119 --> 00:10:21,485
- WHATEVER KEEPS CHEERIOS
ON THE TABLE.
- AMEN TO THAT.

164
00:10:21,554 --> 00:10:24,055
HE CAN RIDE, ZED.
I KNOW SINCE TONY'S BEEN OUT,

165
00:10:24,124 --> 00:10:26,090
YOU'VE BEEN LOOKING
FOR ANOTHER PLAYER.
<i> IS THAT RIGHT?</i>

166
00:10:26,159 --> 00:10:31,262
- YOU UP FOR AN ENDORPHIN FIX?
- IF IT TAKES MORE NAD THAN
LUGING DOWN A CANYON, SURE.

167
00:10:31,331 --> 00:10:36,500
<i> WHY NOT?</i>
WELL, IF YOU GOT 'EM,
BRING 'EM ALONG.

168
00:10:36,569 --> 00:10:39,470
THEN YOU TELL ME.

169
00:10:41,908 --> 00:10:44,542
COME ON, MATES.

170
00:10:45,712 --> 00:10:47,645
<i>[ Zed ]</i>
<i>200 YARDS, HEAD ON.</i>

171
00:10:47,713 --> 00:10:49,647
KEEP YOUR WHEELS
ON THE DOUBLE YELLOW.

172
00:10:49,716 --> 00:10:52,650
IN THE OLD DAYS, THEY USED TO
CALL THIS CHICKEN. I THINK
OF IT MORE OF A CHANCE...

173
00:10:52,718 --> 00:10:54,785
TO, UH, GET A GRIN
FROM THE GODS.

174
00:10:54,854 --> 00:10:57,154
LET'S MAKE THEM SMILE.

175
00:10:59,392 --> 00:11:02,060
LET'S DO IT.

176
00:11:05,965 --> 00:11:09,533
I'M DAMN GOOD, JAROD,
BUT ZED'S GREAT.

177
00:11:09,602 --> 00:11:11,702
DON'T BLINK.
HE'S CAGEABLE.

178
00:11:50,577 --> 00:11:52,743
- OH!
- OOH!

179
00:12:03,189 --> 00:12:06,758
NICE ONE, "J" MAN.
NOT EVEN MY MATE TONY
TOOK ME THAT FAR.

180
00:12:06,826 --> 00:12:08,859
<i> THERE'S A SPOT IN MY TRIBE</i>
<i> IF YOU WANT IT.</i>

181
00:12:08,928 --> 00:12:12,130
MMM.
GOT NOTHIN' BETTER TO DO.

182
00:12:22,542 --> 00:12:26,110
YOU KNOW, I'VE NEVER SEEN ZED
TAKE TO ANYBODY SO FAST, JAROD.

183
00:12:26,179 --> 00:12:28,612
EASY COME, EASY GO,
I GUESS.

184
00:12:28,681 --> 00:12:32,016
ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT TONY?
YEAH.

185
00:12:32,085 --> 00:12:36,921
WHO IS THIS GUY?
TONY USED TO HANG WITH
THE GROUP BEFORE I GOT HERE.

186
00:12:36,990 --> 00:12:40,191
THEN HE GOT MESSED UP
IN A BUNGEE ACCIDENT
A LITTLE OVER A MONTH AGO.

187
00:12:40,259 --> 00:12:42,760
<i> DID HIS CORD BREAK?</i>

188
00:12:42,829 --> 00:12:46,131
FRAYED OR SOMETHING
WHILE TAKIN' A PLUNGE
OFF THE PARKER'S MILL ROAD.

189
00:12:46,199 --> 00:12:49,266
THE DOCTORS DON'T GIVE HIM
MUCH OF A CHANCE.

190
00:12:49,335 --> 00:12:54,471
BUT, HEY,
LIKE ZED ALWAYS SAYS,
FIRST ONE TO 40 ALIVE LOSES.

191
00:12:54,540 --> 00:12:56,240
"J" MAN!

192
00:12:56,309 --> 00:12:58,776
I'M REALLY GLAD
YOU MADE IT TONIGHT.

193
00:12:58,845 --> 00:13:00,878
I DON'T KNOW IF SHAY TOLD YOU,
BUT FRIDAY NIGHTS...

194
00:13:00,947 --> 00:13:03,180
WE DON'T EXACTLY
SQUARE DANCE AROUND THE RADIO.

195
00:13:03,249 --> 00:13:05,649
WE LIKE TO TRY NEW THINGS,
PUSH THE ENVELOPE.

196
00:13:05,718 --> 00:13:08,586
THEN LET'S MAKE THE GODS GRIN.
NO, NO, NO.

197
00:13:08,654 --> 00:13:11,389
LET'S MAKE 'EM LAUGH OUT LOUD.
<i> [ Man ]</i>
<i> WHOO!</i>

198
00:13:17,697 --> 00:13:19,897
FREE THE BRAIN, FREE THE BODY.

199
00:13:19,966 --> 00:13:23,067
FREE THE BODY, FREE THE SOUL.

200
00:13:27,841 --> 00:13:30,107
AND YOU THOUGHT WE WERE GOIN'
HANG GLIDIN' TONIGHT, "J."

201
00:13:38,918 --> 00:13:44,589
FIRE WALKERS IN MAURITIUS LEARN
HOW TO CHANNEL THEIR FEARS,
HARNESS THEM,

202
00:13:44,657 --> 00:13:48,859
TO CREATE A POWER
THAT COULD NOT BE DENIED.

203
00:13:51,931 --> 00:13:54,865
IT'S A POWER
FREE FOR THE TAKING.

204
00:13:54,934 --> 00:13:58,335
NOTHING IS FREE.

205
00:14:36,910 --> 00:14:39,477
I'M STARTIN' TO THINK
YOU'RE A SLAVE
TO THE SAME DEMONS I AM, "J."

206
00:14:39,546 --> 00:14:43,047
WITHOUT DEMONS,
THERE CAN BE NO ANGELS.

207
00:14:43,115 --> 00:14:46,050
F.Y.I.

208
00:14:47,587 --> 00:14:52,222
BASALTIC ROCK.
IT'S A MUCH BETTER
CONDUCTOR OF HEAT.

209
00:14:52,291 --> 00:14:55,592
IF YOU'RE GOING
TO FREE YOUR SOUL,
I SAY FREE IT.

210
00:15:02,602 --> 00:15:05,503
<i>I GUESS OUR CHINESE DINNER WAS</i>
<i>OFFICIALLY A ZONK LAST NIGHT.</i>

211
00:15:05,572 --> 00:15:07,872
ANY RESULTS YET
ON THAT DINNER BILL
FROM THE FORTUNE COOKIE?

212
00:15:07,941 --> 00:15:12,077
WELL, MY PAL BODIE
DOWN IN PHYSICAL
DID A RUSH JOB FOR ME.

213
00:15:12,145 --> 00:15:13,979
THE GEEK WITH
CLOUDY CATARACTS?
YEAH.

214
00:15:14,047 --> 00:15:16,447
HAVE YOU SEEN THEM LATELY?
IT'S MILKIER THAN A GUERNSEY.

215
00:15:16,516 --> 00:15:19,917
SAYS THE KIDS LOVE IT
ON HALLOWEEN.
SOME ZOMBIE THING HE DOES.

216
00:15:19,986 --> 00:15:23,454
THE RESULTS, BROOTS.
UH--

217
00:15:23,523 --> 00:15:27,258
THE-THE ONLY PRINTS ON THE BILL
BELONG TO THE WAITRESS.

218
00:15:27,327 --> 00:15:29,427
MAY, LAST NAME, LIN.

219
00:15:29,496 --> 00:15:32,197
THE ONE WHO QUIT
OVER A MONTH AGO
WITH NO FORWARDING ADDRESS?

220
00:15:32,266 --> 00:15:35,633
LIKE I SAID, ZONK.

221
00:15:35,701 --> 00:15:38,869
OH, MISS PARKER?
JAROD'S DOOR NUMBER TWO
JUST OPENED.

222
00:15:38,938 --> 00:15:40,872
COME SEE WHAT I FOUND INSIDE.

223
00:15:40,941 --> 00:15:43,207
[ Jarod ]
THANK YOU, THANK YOU,
THANK YOU!

224
00:15:43,276 --> 00:15:46,411
IT'S TIME FOR
ANOTHER EXCITING GAME OF
YOU DON'T HAVE A CLUE.

225
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:48,646
I'M YOUR HOST,
JAROD WINKERDALE,

226
00:15:48,715 --> 00:15:51,916
AND IT'S TIME TO SEE
IF YOU HAVE A CLUE.

227
00:15:51,985 --> 00:15:55,119
THIS IS NO STRESS DISORDER, SYD.
IT'S CHERNOBYL OF THE BRAIN.

228
00:15:55,188 --> 00:16:00,258
TODAY'S LUCKY CONTESTANT
IS MISS PARKER!

229
00:16:00,327 --> 00:16:02,527
<i> SHE'LL HAVE OVERNIGHT</i>
<i> TO FIGURE OUT HER CLUE.</i>

230
00:16:02,596 --> 00:16:06,297
AND IF SHE DOES, SHE'LL WIN
A TRIP TO THE BEAUTIFUL
CABINS O' LOVE HIDEAWAY...

231
00:16:06,366 --> 00:16:11,002
NESTLED INTO THE ROLLING HILLS
OF THOMPSON, WEST VIRGINIA.

232
00:16:11,071 --> 00:16:13,237
DON'T LOOK AT ME.
I WATCH SOAPS.

233
00:16:13,306 --> 00:16:16,675
<i> OKAY, MISS PARKER,</i>
<i> HERE'S YOUR CLUE.</i>

234
00:16:16,743 --> 00:16:19,110
THE HIDDEN TRUTH MAY BE MISSING,

235
00:16:19,178 --> 00:16:23,915
BUT YOU WON'T FIND IT
UNTIL YOU CLAIM YOUR PRIZE.

236
00:16:23,984 --> 00:16:27,051
[ Bell Dings ]
"THE HIDDEN TRUTH."

237
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:30,421
THE NAME OF THE RESTAURANT.
"MAY. MAY MISSING."

238
00:16:30,490 --> 00:16:33,358
THE WAITRESS MAY LIN
IS MISSING.

239
00:16:33,426 --> 00:16:36,628
"YOU WON'T FIND IT
UNTIL YOU CLAIM YOUR PRIZE."

240
00:16:36,697 --> 00:16:40,131
A TRIP TO THE BEAUTIFUL
CABINS 0' LOVE.

241
00:16:40,200 --> 00:16:41,866
BEAUTIFUL INDEED.

242
00:17:00,687 --> 00:17:02,720
<i>[ Tony's Mother's Voice ]</i>
<i>TONY'S WALLET HAD BEEN LOST</i>
<i>IN THE ACCIDENT,</i>

243
00:17:02,788 --> 00:17:06,557
<i>BUT SOMEBODY FOUND IT</i>
<i>AT THE NURSES' STATION</i>
<i>THIS MORNING.</i>

244
00:17:06,626 --> 00:17:09,894
<i>IT WAS LEFT IN THAT ENVELOPE</i>
<i>WRAPPED IN WAX PAPER.</i>

245
00:17:16,703 --> 00:17:20,037
- FOUR BUCKS.
- THESE ARE DELICIOUS.

246
00:17:20,106 --> 00:17:24,375
OUGHTA BE.
HARRY'S GOT THE DIRTIEST
DIRTY WATER DOGS IN TOWN.

247
00:17:24,444 --> 00:17:26,844
FOUR DUCKIES.

248
00:17:26,913 --> 00:17:30,081
MY WALLET.

249
00:17:30,149 --> 00:17:32,917
- HAVE YOU SEEN MY WALLET?
- HOW WOULD I KNOW WHERE IT IS?

250
00:17:32,986 --> 00:17:35,353
WELL, SINCE YOU HAVE SUCH
A KNACK FOR FINDING WALLETS,

251
00:17:35,421 --> 00:17:37,655
I THOUGHT MAYBE YOU KNEW
WHERE MINE WAS.

252
00:17:37,724 --> 00:17:40,891
<i>LOOK, WHEN I SAW ON THE NEWS...</i>

253
00:17:40,960 --> 00:17:44,362
THAT THE GUY WAS IN A COMA
FROM THAT BUNGEE ACCIDENT,
I FELT GUILTY.

254
00:17:44,431 --> 00:17:47,432
OH, AN HONORABLE THIEF.
I DIDN'T ROB HIM.
I FOUND IT.

255
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:52,403
ABOUT A MONTH AGO IN THE BUSHES
WHEN I WAS SWEEPIN' UP GLASS.
INDUSTRIAL-GRADE GLASS.

256
00:17:52,472 --> 00:17:55,239
IT WAS ON THE SIDEWALK
BELOW THAT HIGH-RISE THERE.

257
00:17:55,308 --> 00:17:58,943
<i>THE MORNING AFTER THE ROBBERY,</i>
<i>A RARE COIN DEALER</i>
<i>ON THE 30th FLOOR.</i>

258
00:17:59,012 --> 00:18:03,948
A BUNCH OF 'EM ZIP-LINED
FROM THAT BUILDING THROUGH
THE WINDOWS TO THAT ONE.

259
00:18:04,016 --> 00:18:06,283
YOU'D HAVE TO BE CRAZY
TO TRY A STUNT LIKE THAT.

260
00:18:06,352 --> 00:18:08,920
OR SEARCHING FOR YOUR SOUL.

261
00:18:23,836 --> 00:18:26,237
<i>[ Door Closes ]</i>

262
00:19:03,009 --> 00:19:05,309
<i> JAROD, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?</i>

263
00:19:05,378 --> 00:19:08,413
I WAS LOOKING FOR A WRENCH.
MY-MY BIKE'S LOSING COMPRESSION.

264
00:19:08,481 --> 00:19:12,083
<i>AND YOU?</i>
OH, UH, I THOUGHT
YOU WERE ZED.

265
00:19:14,020 --> 00:19:16,687
DID YOU TAKE THIS PICTURE?

266
00:19:16,756 --> 00:19:19,324
<i> NO.</i>
<i> BEFORE I GOT HERE.</i>

267
00:19:19,392 --> 00:19:22,794
<i>IS THAT TONY?</i>
YEAH.

268
00:19:22,863 --> 00:19:27,165
<i> I-I GUESS. ZED USED TO</i>
<i> TALK ABOUT HIM ALL THE TIME</i>
<i> RIGHT AFTER THE ACCIDENT.</i>

269
00:19:27,233 --> 00:19:29,167
MORE THAN HE DOES NOW.

270
00:19:29,236 --> 00:19:31,936
TONY AND ZED,
THEY WERE REALLY GOOD FRIENDS?

271
00:19:32,005 --> 00:19:34,939
TONY WAS IN ZED'S INNER GROUP.

272
00:19:35,008 --> 00:19:37,474
<i> SEE, WITH ZED</i>
<i> IT'S ALL ABOUT</i>
<i> THE ULTIMATE THRILL,</i>

273
00:19:37,543 --> 00:19:41,612
PUSHING THE ENVELOPE,
CHALLENGING THE PEOPLE AROUND
HIM TO FIND THEIR TRUE SELVES.

274
00:19:41,681 --> 00:19:44,815
<i>WHEN HE THINKS YOU'RE READY,</i>
<i>HE INVITES YOU ON</i>
<i>THE ULTIMATE THRILL.</i>

275
00:19:44,884 --> 00:19:47,719
ULTIMATE THRILL,
OR ULTIMATE TEST?

276
00:19:47,787 --> 00:19:50,387
- BOTH, I GUESS.
- HAVE YOU BEEN INVITED?

277
00:19:52,124 --> 00:19:55,192
- I GUESS HE DOESN'T THINK
I'M READY YET.
- AND TONY?

278
00:19:55,261 --> 00:19:59,797
<i>WAS THAT THE ULTIMATE THRILL,</i>
<i>OR THE ULTIMATE TEST?</i>

279
00:19:59,866 --> 00:20:04,134
I DON'T KNOW.
IF YOU'RE NOT IN,
YOU'RE NOT IN.

280
00:20:04,203 --> 00:20:08,239
<i> WELL, I DIDN'T MEAN</i>
<i> TO INTERRUPT.</i>

281
00:20:08,308 --> 00:20:10,241
[ Forced Chuckle ]
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

282
00:20:11,544 --> 00:20:14,912
- SO WHEN DOES ALL
THIS FUN BEGIN?
- MEANING?

283
00:20:14,981 --> 00:20:17,381
MEANING I'M NOT HANGING
AROUND HERE FOR MY HEALTH.

284
00:20:17,450 --> 00:20:20,417
THE ONLY PEOPLE AROUND HERE
WHO ARE HAVING ANY FUN ARE YOU
AND YOUR MERRY LITTLE MEN.

285
00:20:20,486 --> 00:20:23,320
WELL, THOSE MERRY LITTLE MEN
ARE SPECIAL PEOPLE, JAROD.

286
00:20:23,389 --> 00:20:26,056
PEOPLE WHO HAVE PROVEN
THEMSELVES, YOU KNOW?

287
00:20:26,125 --> 00:20:29,260
- PUSHED THE LIMITS OF BOTH
MIND AND BODY.
- AND THE LAW?

288
00:20:29,328 --> 00:20:34,098
YOUR TOYS, THEY WEREN'T
EXACTLY DROPPED OFF
BY SANTA CLAUS, WERE THEY?

289
00:20:34,167 --> 00:20:37,668
LIKE I SAID, "J,"
WHATEVER IT TAKES TO PUT
CHEERIOS ON THE TABLE.

290
00:20:39,572 --> 00:20:41,906
DO YOU THINK YOU HAVE
WHAT IT TAKES, JAROD?

291
00:20:41,975 --> 00:20:44,909
I DON'T KNOW.
WHY DON'T YOU BE THE JUDGE?

292
00:20:50,316 --> 00:20:54,418
IT'S SIMPLE, "J."
I DUMP YOU IN THE WATER,
THEN I THROW IN A KEY.

293
00:20:54,487 --> 00:20:57,888
OBJECT: FREE YOURSELF
BEFORE YOU DIE.

294
00:20:57,957 --> 00:21:00,691
- ZED, THIS IS TOO FAR.
- A CLOSED MIND IS
A CRIPPLED MIND, SHAY.

295
00:21:00,760 --> 00:21:03,761
MAKE FEAR WORK FOR YOU.
CONQUER IT.

296
00:21:03,830 --> 00:21:07,198
JAROD KNOWS.
YOU HAVE TO TASTE DEATH
TO LIVE LIFE.

297
00:21:07,267 --> 00:21:10,401
RIGHT?
OH, I ALMOST FORGOT.

298
00:21:16,109 --> 00:21:20,044
CAN YOU CONQUER THE FEAR, "J"?
YOU'D BE SURPRISED
WHAT I CAN DO.

299
00:21:50,776 --> 00:21:53,411
- ONE MINUTE.
- GIVE HIM THE KEY.

300
00:21:53,479 --> 00:21:56,714
HE'S JUST GETTIN' STARTED,
MY LOVE.

301
00:21:59,319 --> 00:22:01,586
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
LIKE THE ADS SAY,

302
00:22:01,655 --> 00:22:03,587
HELPING HIM BE
ALL THAT HE CAN BE.

303
00:22:06,126 --> 00:22:09,026
HOW ABOUT YOU, SHAY?
HOW FAR WILL YOU PUSH IT
TO BE YOUR BEST?

304
00:22:13,266 --> 00:22:16,033
NINETY SECONDS.

305
00:22:36,522 --> 00:22:39,289
TWO MINUTES.

306
00:22:39,358 --> 00:22:42,293
NO.
HE DON'T WANT HELP.

307
00:22:42,362 --> 00:22:44,262
2:15.

308
00:22:52,137 --> 00:22:55,006
[ Coughs ]

309
00:23:01,914 --> 00:23:05,783
MIND CONQUERS BODY.
WELCOME TO
THE OTHER SIDE, "J."

310
00:23:05,851 --> 00:23:08,452
WELCOME TO THE MERRY MEN.

311
00:23:13,259 --> 00:23:16,827
<i> MAY LIN STAYED</i>
<i> IN THIS CABIN HERE.</i>

312
00:23:18,264 --> 00:23:21,933
PERFECT.

313
00:23:22,002 --> 00:23:25,336
<i>I TRIED TO ENGAGE MAY</i>
<i>IN SOME OCCASIONAL CHITCHAT,</i>

314
00:23:25,405 --> 00:23:28,105
BUT THE LITTLE WAITRESS
WAS A BIT STAND-OFFISH.

315
00:23:28,173 --> 00:23:30,841
I CAN'T IMAGINE
WHAT WOULD MAKE HER
UNCOMFORTABLE AROUND HERE.

316
00:23:30,910 --> 00:23:36,113
ME NEITHER.
BUT I GUESS THEM PEOPLE JUST
LIKE TO STICK TO THEMSELVES.

317
00:23:36,181 --> 00:23:38,115
WHAT KIND OF A RACIST COMMENT
IS THAT?

318
00:23:38,184 --> 00:23:41,251
OH, NO.
I'M NOT UNSOPHISTICATED.

319
00:23:41,320 --> 00:23:44,455
I WAS TALKING ABOUT HER GENDER.
SINGLE WOMAN AND SUCH.

320
00:23:46,092 --> 00:23:48,025
YOU'RE UNATTACHED,
AREN'T YOU?

321
00:23:48,093 --> 00:23:52,229
AS UNATTACHED AS YOUR LIMBS
ARE GONNA BE...

322
00:23:52,298 --> 00:23:56,166
IF YOU KEEP EYEBALLING ME
LIKE THAT, MR. DATSUN.

323
00:23:56,235 --> 00:23:58,336
WELL, ANYHOO,

324
00:23:58,404 --> 00:24:04,074
MAY LIN UP AND VAMOOSED
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT,
SKIPPIN' ON HER BILL.

325
00:24:04,143 --> 00:24:09,947
LEFT HER STUFF BEHIND TOO--
THREE DRESSES, FOUR TOPS,
SHOES, SOCKS, COSMETICS,

326
00:24:10,016 --> 00:24:12,983
AND SIX PAIR OF...
LITTLE BLACK PANTIES.

327
00:24:15,221 --> 00:24:17,488
WELL, I HAD
TO INVENTORY IT.

328
00:24:18,925 --> 00:24:20,858
I BET YOU DID.
KINDA CREEPY.

329
00:24:20,927 --> 00:24:24,661
PRETTY GIRL LIKE THAT
JUST VANISHIN' AND ALL.

330
00:24:24,730 --> 00:24:26,830
YEAH. CREEPY.

331
00:24:39,679 --> 00:24:42,813
A GOOD WRENCH IS HARD
TO COME BY, ISN'T IT,

332
00:24:44,317 --> 00:24:47,451
CARRIE?

333
00:24:47,520 --> 00:24:49,453
[ Chuckles ]
HOW'D YOU KNOW?

334
00:24:49,522 --> 00:24:53,223
THE PAIN IN YOUR EYES
WHEN YOU SAW YOUR BROTHER
IN THIS PICTURE.

335
00:24:53,292 --> 00:24:57,428
TONY IS YOUR BROTHER.
YOUR MOTHER IS
VERY WORRIED ABOUT YOU.

336
00:24:57,497 --> 00:24:59,864
I'M GONNA FIND OUT
WHAT HAPPENED TO TONY.

337
00:24:59,932 --> 00:25:03,534
NOW, I KNOW ZED IS RESPONSIBLE.
I JUST CAN'T PROVE IT YET.

338
00:25:03,602 --> 00:25:05,636
ZED IS NOT SOMEONE
THAT YOU MESS WITH.

339
00:25:05,704 --> 00:25:07,971
NOW, HE TALKS A MEAN GAME
ABOUT LIFE AND ABOUT DEATH,

340
00:25:08,040 --> 00:25:10,474
BUT WHEN PUSH COMES TO SHOVE,
YOU'LL BE THE ONE
DOING THE DYING.

341
00:25:10,543 --> 00:25:13,310
I'M HERE TO HELP YOU.
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO TRUST ME.

342
00:25:18,851 --> 00:25:22,653
TONY TOLD ME THAT
HE MET THIS--

343
00:25:22,722 --> 00:25:26,491
HE MET THIS GUY NAMED ZED,
WHO PROMISED TO HELP HIM
FIND OUR FATHER.

344
00:25:26,559 --> 00:25:28,992
<i> HE SAID HE USED TO RIDE</i>
<i> WITH DAD BACK IN '96.</i>

345
00:25:29,061 --> 00:25:32,830
TONY TRUSTED HIM.
HE BELIEVED HIM.

346
00:25:32,899 --> 00:25:35,199
WHAT HAPPENED?

347
00:25:35,268 --> 00:25:37,768
A MONTH AGO,
THE NIGHT OF TONY'S ACCIDENT,
HE CALLED ME.

348
00:25:37,837 --> 00:25:40,171
<i> I TOLD HIM THAT</i>
<i> OUR MOTHER GOT A CALL</i>
<i> FROM OUR GRANDMOTHER,</i>

349
00:25:40,239 --> 00:25:42,473
AND THEY HADN'T SPOKEN
IN YEARS.

350
00:25:42,542 --> 00:25:45,809
SHE SAID MY FATHER
DIED IN '92.

351
00:25:45,878 --> 00:25:48,246
THAT'S WAY BEFORE ZED
CLAIMS HE KNEW HIM.

352
00:25:48,314 --> 00:25:50,414
SO ZED WAS STRINGING
YOUR BROTHER ALONG.

353
00:25:50,483 --> 00:25:54,818
TONY GOT REALLY ANGRY,
AND HE SAID
HE WAS GONNA CONFRONT ZED.

354
00:25:54,887 --> 00:25:56,821
BUT I GUESS
HE NEVER GOT THE CHANCE.

355
00:25:56,889 --> 00:26:00,925
MAYBE HE DID.
CARRIE, YOU ARE IN
WAY OVER YOUR HEAD.

356
00:26:00,993 --> 00:26:02,693
<i>I WANT YOU TO GO HOME</i>
<i>AND BE WITH YOUR FAMILY.</i>

357
00:26:02,762 --> 00:26:06,864
- I'LL FIND OUT WHAT REALLY
HAPPENED TO YOUR BROTHER.
- NO!

358
00:26:06,933 --> 00:26:08,866
NO WAY.
ALL RIGHT.

359
00:26:08,935 --> 00:26:11,002
YOU MESS WITH MY FAMILY,
YOU MESS WITH ME.

360
00:26:11,070 --> 00:26:14,805
CARRIE, LISTEN TO ME.
I DON'T EVEN KNOW WHO YOU ARE.

361
00:26:14,874 --> 00:26:19,610
<i>I HAVE NO IDEA</i>
<i>HOW YOU GOT INVOLVED IN THIS,</i>
<i>JAROD, BUT... I LIKE YOU.</i>

362
00:26:19,679 --> 00:26:23,181
<i> SO DON'T CROSS ME.</i>
<i> PLEASE?</i>

363
00:26:29,956 --> 00:26:32,523
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>FIND ANYTHING AT</i>
<i>THE CABINS O' LOVE?</i>

364
00:26:32,592 --> 00:26:36,794
YEAH. HOW TO RUIN A PAIR
OF GUCCI'S WITH RED CLAY.

365
00:26:36,862 --> 00:26:40,631
YEAH, THAT'S FUNNY.
THE ENTIRE TRIP
WAS A REGULAR LAUGH RIOT,

366
00:26:40,700 --> 00:26:43,734
THANKS TO JAROD'S
WHACKED-OUT RENDITION
OF ALEX TREBEK.

367
00:26:43,802 --> 00:26:46,370
<i> IT'S MONTY HALL.</i>

368
00:26:46,439 --> 00:26:48,872
<i> [ Buzzer Sounds ]</i>

369
00:26:48,941 --> 00:26:52,309
NO TIME LIKE THE PRESENT
TO FIND OUT
JUST HOW WHACKED-OUT.

370
00:26:56,349 --> 00:26:58,382
WHAT IS IT?

371
00:26:58,450 --> 00:27:01,352
SOMETHING FOR YOU TO CLEAN UP
YOUR THEORIES WITH.

372
00:27:01,421 --> 00:27:04,088
<i> THERE'S A NOTE.</i>

373
00:27:04,156 --> 00:27:06,523
"BE CAREFUL WHAT YOU DIG FOR."

374
00:27:06,592 --> 00:27:09,326
THERE'S AN ADDRESS ON HERE.

375
00:27:09,394 --> 00:27:12,029
- IT'S LYLE'S ADDRESS.
- HUH.

376
00:27:12,098 --> 00:27:14,865
HMM.

377
00:27:18,003 --> 00:27:21,305
<i>SO, LOVE, IT'S UP TO YOU.</i>
<i>WHAT DO YOU SAY?</i>

378
00:27:21,373 --> 00:27:25,042
"J." SAME INVITE STANDS
FOR YOU AS IT DOES FOR SHAY.

379
00:27:25,111 --> 00:27:26,877
- INVITE?
- YEAH.

380
00:27:26,946 --> 00:27:29,814
GOT A JUICY LITTLE EXCURSION
TO THE OTHER SIDE
PLANNED FOR TONIGHT.

381
00:27:29,882 --> 00:27:33,383
THAT IS, IF YOU'RE UP TO IT.

382
00:27:33,452 --> 00:27:38,956
ANYTHING JAROD CAN HANDLE,
I CAN TOO.
EVEN DEATH?

383
00:27:40,326 --> 00:27:42,626
<i>AS THE ANCIENTS SAID,</i>

384
00:27:42,695 --> 00:27:46,330
WHEN THE GODS CREATED MAN,
THEY SAW DEATH
AND SAVED LIFE FOR THEMSELVES.

385
00:27:46,398 --> 00:27:50,634
I SAY,
SINCE WE CAN'T LIVE FOREVER,
LET'S AT LEAST LIVE.

386
00:27:50,703 --> 00:27:53,704
TIME TO DO BATTLE WITH THE GODS.
PASS TONIGHT'S TEST,

387
00:27:53,772 --> 00:27:56,273
AND THERE'LL BE NO LIMIT.

388
00:28:05,651 --> 00:28:08,252
<i>[ Door Opens, Closes ]</i>

389
00:28:08,321 --> 00:28:11,054
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO DO THIS, CARRIE.

390
00:28:11,124 --> 00:28:13,624
THE NAME IS SHAY.
DON'T FORGET IT.

391
00:28:24,336 --> 00:28:28,105
<i>GOOD NEWS, SHAY. THE OWNERS</i>
<i>OF THE HOUSE AREN'T HOME,</i>
<i>MAKIN' YOUR JOB EASIER.</i>

392
00:28:30,209 --> 00:28:32,642
THERE'S A SET OF BLUEPRINTS
IN THE DESK IN THE OFFICE.

393
00:28:32,711 --> 00:28:35,345
<i>BRING THEM TO ME,</i>
<i>WIN VALUABLE PRIZES.</i>

394
00:28:35,414 --> 00:28:37,681
YOU WANT ME
TO ROB THE HOUSE?

395
00:28:37,750 --> 00:28:40,150
THIS IS NOT
ABOUT STEALIN', LOVE.

396
00:28:40,219 --> 00:28:42,185
THIS IS ABOUT
PUSHIN' THE ENVELOPE.

397
00:28:42,254 --> 00:28:44,321
- SHE'S NOT READY.
- I CAN DO IT!

398
00:28:44,390 --> 00:28:47,691
HEY, I KNOW YOU CAN DO IT.
BUT CAN YOU FEEL IT?

399
00:28:49,595 --> 00:28:51,862
CAN YOU FEEL THE DANGER?

400
00:28:51,931 --> 00:28:55,031
THAT'S YOUR PASSAGE
TO THE OTHER SIDE.

401
00:29:06,879 --> 00:29:09,680
<i> [ Dialing, Line Ringing ]</i>

402
00:29:09,749 --> 00:29:12,282
YEAH, PAC TECH SECURITY?
I'D LIKE TO REPORT A BURGLARY.

403
00:29:12,351 --> 00:29:14,384
1600 SEAWARD.

404
00:29:18,423 --> 00:29:20,957
YOU'RE SENDING HER INTO A DANGER
SHE'S NOT READY FOR.

405
00:29:21,025 --> 00:29:24,794
THERE'S ONLY ONE WAY
TO FIND OUT, YOU KNOW?

406
00:29:24,863 --> 00:29:28,131
UH, HELLO. SORRY.
I JUST MADE
A REAL BIG MISTAKE.

407
00:29:28,200 --> 00:29:31,033
IT WAS JUST MY DAUGHTER
COMING HOME LATE WITHOUT A KEY.

408
00:29:31,103 --> 00:29:33,336
YOU'RE MESSIN' WITH MY GAME.
JUST TRYIN' TO HAVE
A LITTLE FUN.

409
00:29:33,404 --> 00:29:38,908
RAISE THE BAR A LITTLE BIT.
NOTHING LIKE A FEW 911 CALLS
TO SPICE UP THE SOUP.

410
00:29:42,280 --> 00:29:46,482
- GO.
-<i> [ Dogs Barking ]</i>

411
00:29:47,652 --> 00:29:49,352
CIRCLE.

412
00:30:05,003 --> 00:30:06,937
CARRIE?

413
00:30:08,974 --> 00:30:10,907
CARRIE?

414
00:30:41,272 --> 00:30:44,107
<i> [ Grunting ]</i>

415
00:30:44,176 --> 00:30:46,910
IT'S ME! IT'S ME!
IT'S ME.
JAROD!

416
00:30:46,978 --> 00:30:51,147
I DID IT.
I GOT THE BLUEPRINTS.
YOU'RE BLEEDING.

417
00:30:51,216 --> 00:30:54,050
I CUT MYSELF
BREAKING IN, AND--

418
00:30:56,888 --> 00:30:58,654
<i> FREEZE! POLICE!</i>

419
00:30:58,723 --> 00:31:01,924
DAMN IT!

420
00:31:01,993 --> 00:31:03,593
GO THAT WAY!

421
00:31:10,635 --> 00:31:13,135
STOP!

422
00:31:13,204 --> 00:31:15,505
<i> GO, GO, GO!</i>
<i> MOVE IT!</i>

423
00:31:51,309 --> 00:31:54,377
"J" MAN. THE CHEERIOS
ARE IN THE CUPBOARD.

424
00:31:54,446 --> 00:31:58,414
DAMN THING STARTED BLEEDING
AGAIN. I WAS LOOKING
FOR SOMETHING TO STOP IT UP.

425
00:31:58,483 --> 00:32:01,717
YEAH, WELL, THERE'S NO THRILL
IN BLEEDIN' TO DEATH,
IS THERE?

426
00:32:02,954 --> 00:32:06,355
YOU KNOW, WHETHER IT'S
A SUICIDE LUNGE,

427
00:32:06,424 --> 00:32:08,590
BUNGEE DIVE,
IT'S ALL ABOUT TRUST...

428
00:32:08,659 --> 00:32:10,793
IN YOURSELF
AND THE ONES AROUND YOU.

429
00:32:10,862 --> 00:32:13,929
- TRUST IS KEY.
- EXACTLY.

430
00:32:13,998 --> 00:32:17,266
- FIRST AID KIT'S IN
THE BATHROOM DOWN THE HALL.
- THANK YOU.

431
00:32:23,175 --> 00:32:25,308
<i>[ Monitor Beeping ]</i>

432
00:32:59,177 --> 00:33:01,844
IT'S ME. SHH. IT'S JAROD.
WE'RE GETTING OUT OF HERE.

433
00:33:01,913 --> 00:33:04,480
JAROD, ZED'S BEEN ASKING
FOR YOU ALL NIGHT.
IT'S ALMOST TIME.

434
00:33:04,549 --> 00:33:08,083
FOR WHAT, HIS FINAL CHALLENGE?
YOU'RE COMING WITH ME.
FORGET IT!

435
00:33:08,152 --> 00:33:11,921
IF THIS SON OF A BITCH IS
RESPONSIBLE FOR MY BROTHER'S
COMA, I HAVE TO PROVE IT.

436
00:33:11,990 --> 00:33:14,757
THAT'S GOING TO BE
VERY DIFFICULT FOR YOU
TO DO FROM PRISON.

437
00:33:14,826 --> 00:33:18,027
I FOUND OUT THAT
THE ACME WAREHOUSE IS
A FRONT FOR MONEY LAUNDERING.

438
00:33:18,095 --> 00:33:20,529
HE'S GONNA USE YOU
TO STEAL CASH,

439
00:33:20,598 --> 00:33:23,633
JUST LIKE HE USED YOUR BROTHER
TO ROB THAT COIN DEALER...

440
00:33:23,701 --> 00:33:25,868
THE NIGHT OF YOUR BROTHER'S
SO-CALLED ACCIDENT.

441
00:33:25,937 --> 00:33:28,838
NOW, WE ARE LEAVING.

442
00:33:28,906 --> 00:33:32,141
<i>I DON'T THINK SO, "J."</i>

443
00:33:34,112 --> 00:33:36,712
<i>YOU KNOW, SHAY,</i>
<i>YOUR BROTHER TONY...</i>

444
00:33:36,782 --> 00:33:38,848
WAS THE CALMEST DUDE
I EVER SAW AT 30 STORIES.

445
00:33:38,917 --> 00:33:40,949
YOU, ON THE OTHER HAND,
LOOK A LITTLE PALE.

446
00:33:41,018 --> 00:33:44,854
<i>BUT THAT'S ALL RIGHT,</i>
<i>'CAUSE I ONLY NEED YOU AS</i>
<i>A SACRIFICIAL LAMB RIGHT NOW.</i>

447
00:33:44,922 --> 00:33:47,490
ISN'T THAT RIGHT, DOC?
JOJO FOLLOWED YOU
TO THE HOSPITAL.

448
00:33:47,559 --> 00:33:52,461
I DON'T KNOW WHO YOU ARE, BUT
THIS DIFFERENT IDENTITY SCENE
MUST BE A RUSH, HUH?

449
00:33:52,530 --> 00:33:53,996
LET'S GO.

450
00:33:55,433 --> 00:33:57,566
NOW I KNOW WHAT TONY
MUST HAVE FELT...

451
00:33:57,635 --> 00:34:00,402
WHEN YOU PUSHED HIM
OFF THAT BRIDGE WEARING
THAT FAULTY BUNGEE CORD.

452
00:34:00,471 --> 00:34:04,307
- THIS SIDE WON'T BE THE SAME
WITHOUT YOU, "J."
- WEIGHTS ARE IN, ZEDDIE.

453
00:34:06,043 --> 00:34:08,344
GIVE MY BEST TO
THE BEAST OF THE GODS.

454
00:34:14,452 --> 00:34:17,520
HE'LL DIE!
BRING HER WITH.

455
00:34:17,588 --> 00:34:19,721
YOU---

456
00:35:02,099 --> 00:35:04,567
[ Gasping ]

457
00:35:07,472 --> 00:35:11,240
<i> [ Broots ]</i>
<i> I SURE HOPE LYLE</i>
<i> IS STILL ON HIS CAMPOUT.</i>

458
00:35:12,510 --> 00:35:14,843
IT'S STUFFY IN HERE.

459
00:35:14,912 --> 00:35:17,913
BEING HERE
GIVES ME THE CREEPS.
WOW.

460
00:35:17,982 --> 00:35:21,050
HIS DECOR IS LIKE
<i> KUNG FU</i> MEETS<i> THE JETSONS.</i>

461
00:35:26,791 --> 00:35:28,925
[ Sarcastic Chuckle ]

462
00:35:30,662 --> 00:35:34,463
<i>FROM CHINESE RESTAURANTS</i>
<i>TO LOVE LODGES...</i>

463
00:35:34,532 --> 00:35:37,733
<i> TO THIS</i> GQ<i> SPREAD</i>
<i> FOR ANAL RETENTION,</i>

464
00:35:37,802 --> 00:35:40,135
JAROD'S HAD US RUNNING AROUND
IN HIS GAME SHOW HELL.

465
00:35:40,205 --> 00:35:45,974
- WHY?
- TO FIND A GRAND PRIZE OF SOME
KIND HERE IN LYLE'S APARTMENT.

466
00:35:46,043 --> 00:35:48,177
<i> SOMETHING INCONGRUOUS</i>
<i> WITH THE SURROUNDINGS.</i>

467
00:35:48,246 --> 00:35:50,412
SOMETHING OUT OF PLACE.

468
00:35:50,481 --> 00:35:54,450
A SPECK OF DUST WOULD BE
OUT OF PLACE IN THIS JOINT.

469
00:35:54,519 --> 00:35:57,320
I FOUND HIS CENTRE
EXPENSE REPORT.

470
00:35:58,990 --> 00:36:03,159
YOU CAN LEARN A LOT ABOUT
A MAN BASED ON THE WAY
HE SPENDS HIS MONEY.

471
00:36:03,227 --> 00:36:06,495
LIKE THE FACT THAT
MY THUMBLESS SIBLING RIPS OFF
THE CENTRE FOR EVERYTHING...

472
00:36:06,564 --> 00:36:08,864
FROM SILK STOCKINGS
TO HERBAL LAXATIVES.

473
00:36:08,933 --> 00:36:11,868
LIKES TO DINE OUT TOO.
LOOK AT THAT.

474
00:36:11,936 --> 00:36:15,871
- THERE MUST BE OVER A DOZEN
CHARGES FOR THE HIDDEN TRUTH.
- THAT'S WHERE MAY LIN WORKED.

475
00:36:15,940 --> 00:36:21,043
AND HE HAS CHARGES FROM
THE CABINS 0' LOVE LODGE.

476
00:36:21,112 --> 00:36:23,947
CHECKED OUT THE SAME DAY
MAY LIN VANISHED.

477
00:36:30,354 --> 00:36:33,222
MISS PARKER?

478
00:36:36,393 --> 00:36:39,195
THERE'S TWO SHOVELS HERE.
THEY BOTH HAVE RED CLAY ON THEM.

479
00:36:39,264 --> 00:36:42,999
NOT UNLIKE THE CLAY
YOU FOUND ON YOUR SHOES.

480
00:36:43,067 --> 00:36:46,235
UH-OH.
<i>WHAT?</i>

481
00:36:46,304 --> 00:36:48,237
THERE'S A DOOR.

482
00:37:02,186 --> 00:37:04,187
OW.

483
00:37:06,490 --> 00:37:08,423
I GOT A BAD FEELING ABOUT THIS.

484
00:37:11,095 --> 00:37:14,497
SMILE, BROOTS. WE JUST WON
THE BIG DEAL OF THE DAY.

485
00:37:14,566 --> 00:37:17,065
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>IT'S A SHED, JUST LIKE</i>
<i>THE ONE JAROD SENT US.</i>

486
00:37:22,740 --> 00:37:25,574
<i>THIS DOESN'T MAKE SENSE.</i>

487
00:37:25,643 --> 00:37:29,745
IT MAKES PERFECT SENSE.
MR. LYLE IS LOCKING
HIMSELF AWAY.

488
00:37:29,814 --> 00:37:31,747
OH. THAT MAKES SENSE?

489
00:37:31,816 --> 00:37:35,218
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>
<i>AS A CHILD,</i>
<i>MR. LYLE'S FOSTER FATHER...</i>

490
00:37:35,286 --> 00:37:38,220
KEPT HIM LOCKED IN A WOODSHED
WEEKS AT A TIME.

491
00:37:38,289 --> 00:37:41,523
<i>WE ALL TRY TO PRESERVE</i>
<i>OUR CHILDHOOD...</i>

492
00:37:41,592 --> 00:37:44,159
<i>WITH ONE RITUAL OR ANOTHER.</i>

493
00:37:44,228 --> 00:37:47,196
<i>IN LYLE'S CASE, THIS WOODSHED</i>
<i>MAY BE THE ONLY PLACE...</i>

494
00:37:47,265 --> 00:37:49,799
<i> IN THE WHOLE WORLD</i>
<i> WHERE HE FEELS SAFE.</i>

495
00:37:49,867 --> 00:37:52,969
- WHAT DOES THAT HAVE TO DO
WITH MAY LIN?
- EVERYTHING.

496
00:37:54,205 --> 00:37:56,938
YOU MEAN HE--
I BELIEVE THE WORD
IS TORTURE.

497
00:37:57,007 --> 00:37:59,408
I BELIEVE THE WORD
IS MURDER.

498
00:37:59,477 --> 00:38:02,044
<i> AND THE</i> JEOPARDY<i> ANSWER</i>
<i> IS HE SLEEPS IN A SHED...</i>

499
00:38:02,113 --> 00:38:04,546
<i> JUST LIKE THE ONE</i>
<i> HE WAS TORTURED IN</i>
<i> WHEN HE WAS LITTLE.</i>

500
00:38:04,615 --> 00:38:07,483
HE STALKS AND KIDNAPS
ASIAN WOMEN,

501
00:38:07,551 --> 00:38:11,887
<i> WHO HE THEN BRINGS TO</i>
<i> A HIDDEN TORTURE CHAMBER.</i>

502
00:38:13,957 --> 00:38:16,625
- WHO IS MR. LYLE?
- OR WHAT?

503
00:38:18,329 --> 00:38:21,130
<i>[ Zed ]</i>
<i>WE'RE ALMOST INTO</i>
<i>THE CASH ROOM, BOYS.</i>

504
00:38:21,199 --> 00:38:23,465
[ Beeping ]
GOT IT. WE'RE IN.

505
00:38:23,534 --> 00:38:26,402
[ Buzzer Sounds ]
IT'S PAYDAY.
GO GET THE CASH.

506
00:38:26,470 --> 00:38:28,470
GO!

507
00:38:43,020 --> 00:38:45,021
[ Gasps ]

508
00:38:46,557 --> 00:38:48,757
SMILE, SHAY.
THIS IS SUPPOSED TO BE
THE FUN PART.

509
00:38:49,828 --> 00:38:52,128
COME ON. LET'S GO.

510
00:38:54,398 --> 00:38:57,999
BEST THRILL YET.
YO, ZEDDIE!

511
00:38:58,068 --> 00:39:01,303
<i>IT'S LOCKED.</i>
<i>COME ON, ZEDDIE!</i>

512
00:39:01,372 --> 00:39:04,807
<i>[ Men Shouting, Indistinct ]</i>

513
00:39:04,875 --> 00:39:09,278
<i>[ Alarm Sounding ]</i>
WHAT IS GOIN' ON HERE?
AAH!

514
00:39:12,550 --> 00:39:14,750
YOU KNOW, IT'S AMAZING
WHAT YOU CAN DO WITH
A PAIR OF WIRE CUTTERS...

515
00:39:14,819 --> 00:39:17,119
AND A GARAGE DOOR
OPENER.

516
00:39:17,188 --> 00:39:21,123
TAKE THESE CUFFS OFF NOW!
THAT WOULDN'T BE ANY FUN.
WHERE'S THE THRILL IN THAT?

517
00:39:21,192 --> 00:39:24,060
<i>SPEAKING OF WHICH,</i>
<i>I GOT A SURPRISE FOR YOU.</i>

518
00:39:24,128 --> 00:39:27,396
JUST...
DON'T GO AWAY.
[ Yells ]

519
00:39:27,465 --> 00:39:30,299
<i> HERE. GO TO YOUR MOM.</i>
<i> SHE'S WORRIED ABOUT YOU.</i>

520
00:39:30,368 --> 00:39:32,535
NOW, GO.

521
00:39:32,603 --> 00:39:34,870
WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU DOING?

522
00:39:34,939 --> 00:39:37,907
I'M GIVING YOU SOMETHING
THAT YOU DIDN'T GIVE TONY--
A CHANCE.

523
00:39:37,975 --> 00:39:40,576
SLIM, BUT A CHANCE.

524
00:39:45,082 --> 00:39:48,050
- WHAT'S GOING ON, "J"?
- THE ULTIMATE THRILL.

525
00:39:48,118 --> 00:39:53,221
THE ULTIMATE TEST.
OR SHOULD I SAY,
THE ULTIMATE SPLAT?

526
00:39:54,559 --> 00:39:58,194
WOW. THIS CORD IS SO OLD.
I DON'T--

527
00:39:58,263 --> 00:40:01,597
I DON'T KNOW IF IT'S GONNA
MAKE IT THROUGH ANOTHER JUMP.
OH, WELL, LIKE YOU SAY:

528
00:40:01,665 --> 00:40:05,333
[ Imitating Zed ]
"IT'S TIME TO DO BATTLE
WITH THE BEAST OF THE GODS."

529
00:40:05,402 --> 00:40:08,370
- PULL ME UP, "J," NOW!
- OH, CAN YOU FEEL IT?

530
00:40:08,439 --> 00:40:12,575
<i> CAN YOU FEEL THE FEAR?</i>
<i> THAT'S YOUR TICKET</i>
<i> TO THE ULTIMATE THRILL.</i>

531
00:40:12,643 --> 00:40:15,110
YEAH!
GET ME DOWN FROM HERE!

532
00:40:15,179 --> 00:40:18,680
DID YOU GIVE TONY GOLTZ
THAT CHANCE?
HE TRUSTED YOU.

533
00:40:18,749 --> 00:40:21,917
HE TRUSTED YOU
TO FIND THE FATHER THAT
HE'D BEEN SEARCHING FOR.

534
00:40:21,986 --> 00:40:25,754
<i>HE FOUND OUT YOU LIED TO HIM,</i>
<i>THAT YOU WERE JUST USING HIM,</i>
<i>TURNING HIM INTO A THIEF.</i>

535
00:40:25,823 --> 00:40:28,623
TONY WAS GUTSY...
BUT STUPID.

536
00:40:28,692 --> 00:40:30,660
HE WAS GOING TO TURN YOU
INTO THE POLICE,

537
00:40:30,728 --> 00:40:33,929
SO YOU TIED HIM TO
A FAULTY BUNGEE CORD AND
YOU TOSSED HIM TO HIS DEATH.

538
00:40:33,998 --> 00:40:36,265
ONLY HE DIDN'T DIE, DID HE?

539
00:40:36,334 --> 00:40:39,635
NOW HE'S LYING IN A HOSPITAL BED
TRAPPED INSIDE HIS OWN BODY,

540
00:40:39,703 --> 00:40:42,905
AND HE MAY NEVER AGAIN
EXPERIENCE ANOTHER THRILL.

541
00:40:42,973 --> 00:40:46,742
BUT THEN AGAIN,
NEITHER WILL YOU.

542
00:40:46,810 --> 00:40:49,144
<i> NO. NO. NO.</i>

543
00:40:49,213 --> 00:40:51,413
<i> NO. NO!</i>
READY, SET--

544
00:40:51,482 --> 00:40:53,582
<i> OKAY! OKAY!</i>
<i> I DID IT!</i>

545
00:40:53,651 --> 00:40:58,119
<i> I KNEW TONY WAS GONNA GO</i>
<i> TO THE POLICE.</i>
<i> NOW GET ME DOWN FROM HERE!</i>

546
00:40:58,188 --> 00:41:01,623
YOU'D BETTER RELAX, ZED.

547
00:41:01,692 --> 00:41:03,893
- COME ON. YOU FEEL IT?
- YEAH, WELL--

548
00:41:03,962 --> 00:41:07,796
YOU FEEL THE DANGER?
THAT'S YOUR PASSAGE TO
THE OTHER SIDE, REMEMBER?

549
00:41:07,865 --> 00:41:09,765
<i> NO!</i>
ENJOY YOUR JOURNEY.

550
00:41:09,833 --> 00:41:12,434
- NO!
- OH, LIKE YOU SAID:

551
00:41:12,503 --> 00:41:17,173
<i>YOU'VE GOT TO TASTE DEATH</i>
<i>TO EXPERIENCE LIFE.</i>

552
00:41:17,241 --> 00:41:19,975
<i> [ Yelling ]</i>

553
00:41:33,524 --> 00:41:36,292
I GUESS THIS OLD CORD HAD
ONE MORE JUMP IN IT AFTER ALL.

554
00:41:37,895 --> 00:41:40,495
GET ME OUT OF HERE!

555
00:41:44,168 --> 00:41:46,802
IT'S A BEAUTIFUL DAY
IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD.

556
00:41:49,740 --> 00:41:52,841
WHAT? JAROD ATTEND
A MONTY HALL GARAGE SALE?

557
00:41:52,910 --> 00:41:55,544
MR. LYLE,
YOU SEEM SO, UM--

558
00:41:55,613 --> 00:41:58,547
RELAXED?

559
00:41:58,615 --> 00:42:00,849
YEAH, I JUST CAME IN FROM
THE MOUNTAINS. I HEARD
YOU HAD A LEAD ON JAROD.

560
00:42:00,918 --> 00:42:04,853
NO, ALL OF THIS...
WAS A DEAD END.

561
00:42:08,225 --> 00:42:12,394
DIDN'T EVEN<i> SHED</i> ANY LIGHT
ON HIS PERSONALITY, SYD?

562
00:42:12,463 --> 00:42:15,464
NO. NOT ON HIS.

563
00:42:20,338 --> 00:42:22,304
OH, WELL.

564
00:42:23,807 --> 00:42:28,610
UM, NOTHING PERSONAL,
BUT YOU THREE
LOOK TERRIBLE.

565
00:42:28,679 --> 00:42:30,645
YOU SHOULD TAKE A BREAK,
REJUVENATE,

566
00:42:30,714 --> 00:42:34,149
<i>GET INTO THE GREAT OUTDOORS,</i>
<i>RELIEVE SOME OF THAT STRESS.</i>

567
00:42:34,218 --> 00:42:38,020
<i> GOD KNOWS IT MAKES ME FEEL</i>
<i> SO ALIVE.</i>

568
00:42:41,058 --> 00:42:43,759
♪♪ [ Whistling ]

569
00:42:43,827 --> 00:42:46,462
<i> [ Cell Phone Ringing ]</i>

570
00:42:46,531 --> 00:42:48,497
I'M GONNA THROW UP.
WHAT?

571
00:42:48,566 --> 00:42:50,666
ONE OF US HAS TO STOP HIM,
MISS PARKER.

572
00:42:50,735 --> 00:42:54,336
I WAS TOO LATE FOR MAY LIN.
I'LL KEEP MY EYES OPEN.
COUNT ON IT.

573
00:42:54,405 --> 00:42:58,273
JAROD, WE TOOK A HELL OF A RISK
BREAKING INTO LYLE'S APARTMENT.

574
00:42:58,342 --> 00:43:02,444
SOMETIMES, THE RISKS
WE TAKE ARE WORTH IT.

575
00:43:05,582 --> 00:43:10,619
WELL, I'LL SEE YOU NEXT TIME
ON "THE FEUD."

